  <dsc><c id="0a975d3fddb343d58805d8486c61209b" level="series"><did><unitid>1</unitid><unitdate normal="1931/1967" type="inclusive">1931-1967</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_3961eb5bf85cb50170d83c2bdfec6b75"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Within Series 1, there are two groupings of material: the Rockefeller Foundation group and the virus group. The Rockefeller Foundation group consists of material which pertains to Dr. Smith's formal association with the Foundation and his correspondence with members of the Foundation after he retired. Correspondence forms the bulk of the group but there are also reports and diaries included.</p><p>The Series 1 section on viruses contains material from the Rockefeller virus labs as well as Dr. Smith's own activities in arbovirus research in Arizona. It consists mainly of correspondence. Professional interests note a variety of activities in which Dr. Smith was involved either in his association with the University of Arizona or through his membership in medical and public health organizations.</p></scopecontent><arrangement id="aspace_c6dac0ddac5063f1be62e7a74cf7b868"><head>Arrangement</head><p>Series 1 is generally chronological in arrangement.</p></arrangement><c id="c35015cf8c7a4ce7b23ebcd2d14e2dc3" level="file"><did><unittitle>Rockefeller Foundation</unittitle><unitdate normal="1930/1966" type="inclusive">1930-1966</unitdate><container altrender="Letter Document Box" id="cee5146f9b204086b5686661fe5d5d93" label="mixed materials [A0000000068144]" type="box">1</container><container id="ace4ddc1586f26a44f59b20d9fe19eb1" parent="cee5146f9b204086b5686661fe5d5d93" type="folder">1-7</container></did></c><c id="3dcf714526064523b5bad678a0345b79" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Comments on the Future of the International Health Division (IHD)"</unittitle><container altrender="Letter Document Box" id="dc9da5d055c3fe37d03a9253853f1bd8" label="mixed materials [A0000000068144]" type="box">1</container><container id="980887b97d70562cf